    "body": "### Problem\n\n`shiftwidth` unexpectedly changed.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nThe help says\r\n\r\n> Nvim searches all parent directories of that file for \".editorconfig\" files\r\n\r\nbut as seen in the following\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ nvim -V1 /junk/repo/neovim/neovim/runtime/lua/man.lua\r\n\r\n:verbose set sw\r\n\r\nshiftwidth=2                                                                            \r\n      Last set from /junk/install/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/editorconfig.lua line 121          \r\n```\r\nThe file that changes shiftwidth does not match the name as specified in `:help`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`shiftwidth` should not be changed.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev (sept 21 source)\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nnot in vim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nubuntu\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nubuntu\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nmake install",
